{
  "segments": [
    {
      "id": 0,
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 0.5,
      "text": "12."
    },
    {
      "id": 1,
      "start": 3.48,
      "end": 4.48,
      "text": "OK."
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "start": 4.48,
      "end": 7.04,
      "text": "So leading to his question about push versus pull."
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "start": 7.04,
      "end": 8.56,
      "text": "But in all the examples that it showed,"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "start": 8.56,
      "end": 11.92,
      "text": "there was this next function, whether it's"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "start": 11.92,
      "end": 16.16,
      "text": "vectorized, materialized, or iterator."
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "start": 16.16,
      "end": 19.12,
      "text": "There's this next column I'm making on the peropriter."
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "start": 19.12,
      "end": 21.36,
      "text": "And I'm always starting at the top, calling the root,"
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "start": 21.36,
      "end": 24.2,
      "text": "and going down and bringing things up."
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "start": 24.2,
      "end": 26.72,
      "text": "And again, this is how most systems are going to implement"
    },
    {
      "id": 10,
      "start": 26.72,
      "end": 29.92,
      "text": "the extension, but it isn't the only way."
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "start": 29.92,
      "end": 33.12,
      "text": "And this gets into the distinction of top to bottom,"
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "start": 33.12,
      "end": 34.96,
      "text": "the pull-based approach to the bottom top."
    },
    {
      "id": 13,
      "start": 34.96,
      "end": 37.52,
      "text": "So again, the top to bottom is what I just showed."
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "start": 37.52,
      "end": 39.08,
      "text": "If you want to start exceeding the query,"
    },
    {
      "id": 15,
      "start": 39.08,
      "end": 40.52,
      "text": "you call next on the root."
    },
    {
      "id": 16,
      "start": 40.52,
      "end": 43.0,
      "text": "And then that will then call next on its children,"
    },
    {
      "id": 17,
      "start": 43.0,
      "end": 45.08,
      "text": "propagate down, to the pooling data"
    },
    {
      "id": 18,
      "start": 45.08,
      "end": 47.8,
      "text": "from the bottom of the query plan up to the top, to the root."
    },
    {
      "id": 19,
      "start": 47.8,
      "end": 51.56,
      "text": "And that produces the final output."
    },
    {
      "id": 20,
      "start": 51.56,
      "end": 55.96,
      "text": "And you're always going to be calling"
    },
    {
      "id": 21,
      "start": 55.96,
      "end": 58.6,
      "text": "next to get the next tuple, unless it's a pipeline breaker,"
    },
    {
      "id": 22,
      "start": 58.6,
      "end": 60.96,
      "text": "because that'll stage data in a sort of intermediate result"
    },
    {
      "id": 23,
      "start": 60.96,
      "end": 62.52,
      "text": "that you then go access."
    },
    {
      "id": 24,
      "start": 62.52,
      "end": 66.64,
      "text": "But you're always passing data by calling next."
    },
    {
      "id": 25,
      "start": 66.64,
      "end": 68.52,
      "text": "And that's going to be a function call."
    },
    {
      "id": 26,
      "start": 68.52,
      "end": 69.96,
      "text": "That's a jump instruction."
    },
    {
      "id": 27,
      "start": 69.96,
      "end": 73.76,
      "text": "And again, that's bad for a super scaler CPU."
    },
    {
      "id": 28,
      "start": 73.76,
      "end": 76.04,
      "text": "Alternate approach is the push-based model,"
    },
    {
      "id": 29,
      "start": 76.04,
      "end": 80.16,
      "text": "where you start with the leaf nodes in the query plan."
    },
    {
      "id": 30,
      "start": 80.16,
      "end": 83.52,
      "text": "And you have some outside controller or a scheduler"
    },
    {
      "id": 31,
      "start": 83.52,
      "end": 89.04,
      "text": "initiate the invocation of that operator, the pipeline."
    },
    {
      "id": 32,
      "start": 89.04,
      "end": 92.36,
      "text": "And then it's going to take the data that it generates"
    },
    {
      "id": 33,
      "start": 92.36,
      "end": 96.92,
      "text": "and push it to the next operator."
    },
    {
      "id": 34,
      "start": 96.92,
      "end": 97.44,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 35,
      "start": 97.44,
      "end": 99.48,
      "text": "How long do I mean doing this?"
    },
    {
      "id": 36,
      "start": 99.48,
      "end": 100.72,
      "text": "We'll get that in a second."
    },
    {
      "id": 37,
      "start": 100.72,
      "end": 101.92,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 38,
      "start": 101.92,
      "end": 105.48,
      "text": "So this is rare."
    },
    {
      "id": 39,
      "start": 105.48,
      "end": 106.84,
      "text": "It's probably more common now."
    },
    {
      "id": 40,
      "start": 106.84,
      "end": 109.8,
      "text": "But again, when this paper you guys are in 2005,"
    },
    {
      "id": 41,
      "start": 109.8,
      "end": 111.6,
      "text": "this approach didn't exist."
    },
    {
      "id": 42,
      "start": 111.6,
      "end": 112.76,
      "text": "This shows up in a paper that you're"
    },
    {
      "id": 43,
      "start": 112.76,
      "end": 115.92,
      "text": "trying to read in a few weeks from the Germans"
    },
    {
      "id": 44,
      "start": 115.92,
      "end": 117.24,
      "text": "and this system called Hyper."
    },
    {
      "id": 45,
      "start": 117.24,
      "end": 117.96,
      "text": "The dude's insane."
    },
    {
      "id": 46,
      "start": 117.96,
      "end": 119.56,
      "text": "It's a one-person author in paper."
    },
    {
      "id": 47,
      "start": 119.56,
      "end": 121.76,
      "text": "He invented or didn't invent, but he showed"
    },
    {
      "id": 48,
      "start": 121.76,
      "end": 123.48,
      "text": "how to do just the time query compilation"
    },
    {
      "id": 49,
      "start": 123.48,
      "end": 125.32,
      "text": "with the LLVM in Hyper."
    },
    {
      "id": 50,
      "start": 125.32,
      "end": 128.84,
      "text": "Plus also, he invents the push-based model in the paper as well."
    },
    {
      "id": 51,
      "start": 128.84,
      "end": 130.08,
      "text": "And he's got three cleats."
    },
    {
      "id": 52,
      "start": 130.08,
      "end": 133.16,
      "text": "He teaches two classes to a semester."
    },
    {
      "id": 53,
      "start": 133.16,
      "end": 134.08,
      "text": "And he doesn't do drugs."
    },
    {
      "id": 54,
      "start": 134.08,
      "end": 135.08,
      "text": "It's insane."
    },
    {
      "id": 55,
      "start": 135.08,
      "end": 136.08,
      "text": "Right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 56,
      "start": 136.08,
      "end": 138.6,
      "text": "He's the exact opposite."
    },
    {
      "id": 57,
      "start": 138.6,
      "end": 139.6,
      "text": "He's very straight-laced."
    },
    {
      "id": 58,
      "start": 139.6,
      "end": 141.08,
      "text": "Anyway."
    },
    {
      "id": 59,
      "start": 141.08,
      "end": 142.28,
      "text": "So let's see how I do this."
    },
    {
      "id": 60,
      "start": 142.28,
      "end": 144.76,
      "text": "So here's our same query I had before."
    },
    {
      "id": 61,
      "start": 144.76,
      "end": 147.48,
      "text": "And now, here's our two pipelines."
    },
    {
      "id": 62,
      "start": 147.48,
      "end": 149.24,
      "text": "But now, instead of having a bunch of different operators"
    },
    {
      "id": 63,
      "start": 149.24,
      "end": 152.36,
      "text": "that would have the implement the individual, or blocks"
    },
    {
      "id": 64,
      "start": 152.36,
      "end": 154.88,
      "text": "that could implement the individual operators,"
    },
    {
      "id": 65,
      "start": 154.88,
      "end": 158.52,
      "text": "now we're just going to have two forlifts."
    },
    {
      "id": 66,
      "start": 158.52,
      "end": 160.84,
      "text": "And so for the first first pipeline, we're"
    },
    {
      "id": 67,
      "start": 160.84,
      "end": 164.12,
      "text": "going to scan R and then populate the hash table."
    },
    {
      "id": 68,
      "start": 164.12,
      "end": 167.12,
      "text": "But in the second pipeline, we're going to scan S."
    },
    {
      "id": 69,
      "start": 167.12,
      "end": 169.4,
      "text": "And now you can see what we're going to try to do"
    },
    {
      "id": 70,
      "start": 169.4,
      "end": 172.0,
      "text": "is ride every single tuple all the way up"
    },
    {
      "id": 71,
      "start": 172.0,
      "end": 175.56,
      "text": "to the top of the query plan before we go back and look"
    },
    {
      "id": 72,
      "start": 175.56,
      "end": 177.76,
      "text": "at the next tuple or the batch of tuples."
    },
    {
      "id": 73,
      "start": 177.76,
      "end": 178.84,
      "text": "Even though I'm showing this opportunity"
    },
    {
      "id": 74,
      "start": 178.84,
      "end": 182.2,
      "text": "to single tuple, you could do this on a batch as well."
    },
    {
      "id": 75,
      "start": 182.2,
      "end": 185.12,
      "text": "So for every tuple in S, then you bow at the predicate."
    },
    {
      "id": 76,
      "start": 185.12,
      "end": 187.2,
      "text": "If that matches, then you probe the hash table."
    },
    {
      "id": 77,
      "start": 187.2,
      "end": 191.24,
      "text": "Then if that matches, then you put it as the output."
    },
    {
      "id": 78,
      "start": 191.24,
      "end": 191.74,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 79,
      "start": 191.74,
      "end": 193.48,
      "text": "How are we going to get to the future by an alumni?"
    },
    {
      "id": 80,
      "start": 193.48,
      "end": 194.64,
      "text": "This is fusion right here."
    },
    {
      "id": 81,
      "start": 194.64,
      "end": 196.64,
      "text": "So how did that even end up happening?"
    },
    {
      "id": 82,
      "start": 196.64,
      "end": 197.88,
      "text": "Where did it happen?"
    },
    {
      "id": 83,
      "start": 197.88,
      "end": 200.04,
      "text": "It didn't sense that you need one of your structures"
    },
    {
      "id": 84,
      "start": 200.04,
      "end": 201.32,
      "text": "to be an old reader."
    },
    {
      "id": 85,
      "start": 201.32,
      "end": 205.64,
      "text": "So would you be hard to code every single combination?"
    },
    {
      "id": 86,
      "start": 205.64,
      "end": 206.64,
      "text": "You don't hope it is."
    },
    {
      "id": 87,
      "start": 206.64,
      "end": 207.76,
      "text": "It would probably depend on that."
    },
    {
      "id": 88,
      "start": 207.76,
      "end": 208.44,
      "text": "OK."
    },
    {
      "id": 89,
      "start": 208.44,
      "end": 212.72,
      "text": "So his question is basically, how do you do this?"
    },
    {
      "id": 90,
      "start": 212.72,
      "end": 216.2,
      "text": "Would you have to hard code every single possible combination"
    },
    {
      "id": 91,
      "start": 216.2,
      "end": 217.76,
      "text": "of query plans?"
    },
    {
      "id": 92,
      "start": 217.76,
      "end": 218.96,
      "text": "I execute this."
    },
    {
      "id": 93,
      "start": 218.96,
      "end": 220.48,
      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "id": 94,
      "start": 220.48,
      "end": 223.2,
      "text": "So how would you have that?"
    },
    {
      "id": 95,
      "start": 223.2,
      "end": 223.76,
      "text": "That's a very good question."
    },
    {
      "id": 96,
      "start": 223.76,
      "end": 225.36,
      "text": "Two weeks."
    },
    {
      "id": 97,
      "start": 225.36,
      "end": 227.16,
      "text": "The answer is going to be, you know, just in time"
    },
    {
      "id": 98,
      "start": 227.16,
      "end": 230.8,
      "text": "to compile this, you really generate the code on the fly"
    },
    {
      "id": 99,
      "start": 230.8,
      "end": 232.72,
      "text": "for the query plan that fuses this together,"
    },
    {
      "id": 100,
      "start": 232.72,
      "end": 237.28,
      "text": "then compile it with the LLVM of GCC or Clang, then run that."
    },
    {
      "id": 101,
      "start": 237.28,
      "end": 238.8,
      "text": "That's a proctor number one."
    },
    {
      "id": 102,
      "start": 238.8,
      "end": 240.8,
      "text": "A proctor number two is that you recognize,"
    },
    {
      "id": 103,
      "start": 240.8,
      "end": 243.88,
      "text": "I only have so many data types in my database system,"
    },
    {
      "id": 104,
      "start": 243.88,
      "end": 245.92,
      "text": "and there's only so many things I could do to them."
    },
    {
      "id": 105,
      "start": 245.92,
      "end": 248.84,
      "text": "So each of these are just functions, right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 106,
      "start": 248.84,
      "end": 256.0,
      "text": "And I just put them in an array, and I execute one by one."
    },
    {
      "id": 107,
      "start": 256.0,
      "end": 258.0,
      "text": "That's what vector wise does."
    },
    {
      "id": 108,
      "start": 258.0,
      "end": 259.76,
      "text": "That's code specialization."
    },
    {
      "id": 109,
      "start": 259.76,
      "end": 261.6,
      "text": "Give me two weeks."
    },
    {
      "id": 110,
      "start": 261.6,
      "end": 262.92,
      "text": "What did that?"
    },
    {
      "id": 111,
      "start": 262.92,
      "end": 263.92,
      "text": "Right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 112,
      "start": 263.92,
      "end": 264.44,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "id": 113,
      "start": 264.44,
      "end": 265.2,
      "text": "Your mind looks blown."
    },
    {
      "id": 114,
      "start": 265.2,
      "end": 266.68,
      "text": "In fact, you can compile this on the fly."
    },
    {
      "id": 115,
      "start": 266.68,
      "end": 268.16,
      "text": "Yeah, this is what they do."
    },
    {
      "id": 116,
      "start": 268.16,
      "end": 271.16,
      "text": "They're German, right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 117,
      "start": 271.16,
      "end": 271.96,
      "text": "The Swiss are good, too."
    },
    {
      "id": 118,
      "start": 271.96,
      "end": 273.84,
      "text": "Swiss are good, too."
    },
    {
      "id": 119,
      "start": 273.84,
      "end": 277.68,
      "text": "So this is hard, right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 120,
      "start": 277.68,
      "end": 278.48,
      "text": "I don't get too bad."
    },
    {
      "id": 121,
      "start": 278.48,
      "end": 279.44,
      "text": "It's even crazier than that."
    },
    {
      "id": 122,
      "start": 279.44,
      "end": 282.68,
      "text": "The new version, in this version, they"
    },
    {
      "id": 123,
      "start": 282.68,
      "end": 285.52,
      "text": "will, in hyper, they would generate the LLVM IR"
    },
    {
      "id": 124,
      "start": 285.52,
      "end": 286.8,
      "text": "than compile that."
    },
    {
      "id": 125,
      "start": 286.8,
      "end": 289.52,
      "text": "Single-store will generate C code, then compile that."
    },
    {
      "id": 126,
      "start": 289.52,
      "end": 290.72,
      "text": "At least the version."
    },
    {
      "id": 127,
      "start": 290.72,
      "end": 292.18,
      "text": "In the latest version, the new system,"
    },
    {
      "id": 128,
      "start": 292.18,
      "end": 294.12,
      "text": "they're being called Umbra, he doesn't generate IR."
    },
    {
      "id": 129,
      "start": 294.12,
      "end": 297.36,
      "text": "He generates literally x86 assembly."
    },
    {
      "id": 130,
      "start": 297.36,
      "end": 299.92,
      "text": "Like C++ macros, then he runs that through the assembler."
    },
    {
      "id": 131,
      "start": 299.92,
      "end": 302.18,
      "text": "Then on the background, he's running the LLVM,"
    },
    {
      "id": 132,
      "start": 302.18,
      "end": 305.4,
      "text": "compiles the assembly code into a shared object."
    },
    {
      "id": 133,
      "start": 305.4,
      "end": 308.52,
      "text": "And when that's done, he then links it in."
    },
    {
      "id": 134,
      "start": 308.52,
      "end": 309.92,
      "text": "Yeah, German, yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 135,
      "start": 309.92,
      "end": 311.4,
      "text": "So when you're telling the link to Thailand,"
    },
    {
      "id": 136,
      "start": 311.4,
      "end": 313.68,
      "text": "each of those, like, the fixed number of functions"
    },
    {
      "id": 137,
      "start": 313.68,
      "end": 315.76,
      "text": "you have to compile a longer array."
    },
    {
      "id": 138,
      "start": 315.76,
      "end": 316.84,
      "text": "But these are function players."
    },
    {
      "id": 139,
      "start": 317.4,
      "end": 319.52,
      "text": "When you want to use these together,"
    },
    {
      "id": 140,
      "start": 319.52,
      "end": 321.84,
      "text": "like finding this function A, function B,"
    },
    {
      "id": 141,
      "start": 321.84,
      "end": 323.8,
      "text": "and then you, like, rearrange everything"
    },
    {
      "id": 142,
      "start": 323.8,
      "end": 325.44,
      "text": "in your array, so you can actually do that word."
    },
    {
      "id": 143,
      "start": 325.44,
      "end": 327.04,
      "text": "Yes, the question is, the way you want to do this,"
    },
    {
      "id": 144,
      "start": 327.04,
      "end": 330.36,
      "text": "if there are function pointers, would be a bunch of arrays"
    },
    {
      "id": 145,
      "start": 330.36,
      "end": 332.76,
      "text": "where I'm putting in, I need to do this, the file by this,"
    },
    {
      "id": 146,
      "start": 332.76,
      "end": 333.92,
      "text": "file by this."
    },
    {
      "id": 147,
      "start": 333.92,
      "end": 336.44,
      "text": "And then would you just invoke this function pointer"
    },
    {
      "id": 148,
      "start": 336.44,
      "end": 337.0,
      "text": "as you go along?"
    },
    {
      "id": 149,
      "start": 337.0,
      "end": 338.2,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 150,
      "start": 338.2,
      "end": 341.56,
      "text": "And that would suck if you're doing it on a per-tuple basis."
    },
    {
      "id": 151,
      "start": 341.56,
      "end": 343.8,
      "text": "But if you do batches of tuples in the vectorized model,"
    },
    {
      "id": 152,
      "start": 343.8,
      "end": 345.52,
      "text": "then that amortizes the jump call."
    },
    {
      "id": 153,
      "start": 347.8,
      "end": 349.2,
      "text": "And then now you don't have giant switch statements"
    },
    {
      "id": 154,
      "start": 349.2,
      "end": 350.44,
      "text": "of, like, what branch should I go down?"
    },
    {
      "id": 155,
      "start": 350.44,
      "end": 351.28,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 156,
      "start": 351.28,
      "end": 354.36,
      "text": "I cannot wait to do this in a full-base model."
    },
